---
export const prerender = true;
import Shop from '@/layouts/Shop.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '@/components/astro/Breadcrumb.astro';
import { tenant } from '@/config/tenant';

const publishDate = '2026-03-26';
const title = 'What Are Nicotine Pouches? A Complete Guide for Beginners';
const description = 'Learn everything about tobacco-free nicotine pouches — how they work, how to use them, available strengths and flavours, and why millions are switching from traditional tobacco.';
---

<Shop
  title={`${title} | ${tenant.name}`}
  description={description}
  ogType="article"
>
  <article class="bg-background text-foreground">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
      <Breadcrumb items={[
        { label: 'Blog', href: '/blog' },
        { label: 'What Are Nicotine Pouches?' },
      ]} />

      <header class="mb-10">
        <p class="mb-3 text-sm font-medium uppercase tracking-widest text-primary">Guide</p>
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl">{title}</h1>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">{description}</p>
        <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-muted-foreground">
          <time datetime={publishDate}>March 26, 2026</time>
          <span>&middot;</span>
          <span>8 min read</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground [&_h2]:text-foreground [&_h2]:text-2xl [&_h2]:font-bold [&_h2]:mt-10 [&_h2]:mb-4 [&_h3]:text-foreground [&_h3]:text-xl [&_h3]:font-semibold [&_h3]:mt-8 [&_h3]:mb-3 [&_strong]:text-foreground [&_a]:text-primary [&_a]:underline [&_a:hover]:text-foreground">

        <h2>What Are Nicotine Pouches?</h2>
        <p>
          Nicotine pouches are small, pre-portioned sachets that deliver nicotine through
          the lining of your mouth. Unlike traditional snus or chewing tobacco, nicotine
          pouches contain <strong>no tobacco leaf whatsoever</strong>. They are white, discreet, and produce
          no smoke, no vapour, and no spit.
        </p>
        <p>
          Each pouch typically contains pharmaceutical-grade nicotine, plant-based fibres
          (usually cellulose), flavouring, and a pH adjuster that helps the nicotine absorb
          efficiently. You place one pouch between your upper lip and gum, leave it there for
          20 to 40 minutes, then remove and dispose of it.
        </p>

        <h2>How Do Nicotine Pouches Work?</h2>
        <p>
          When the pouch rests against your gum, moisture activates the ingredients. Nicotine
          is released gradually and absorbed through the oral mucosa — the soft tissue inside
          your mouth. Most users feel the effect within 1 to 5 minutes, with a tingling
          sensation that settles after the first few uses.
        </p>
        <p>
          Because there is no combustion or heating involved, nicotine pouches avoid the
          thousands of harmful chemicals produced by burning tobacco. This is a key reason
          public health researchers consider them a reduced-risk alternative.
        </p>

        <h2>Available Strengths</h2>
        <p>
          Nicotine pouches come in a wide range of strengths to suit different preferences
          and experience levels:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><a href="/products/strength/light"><strong>Light (2-4 mg)</strong></a> — Ideal for beginners or those who want subtle, all-day use</li>
          <li><a href="/products/strength/normal"><strong>Normal (4-8 mg)</strong></a> — The most popular range for everyday users</li>
          <li><a href="/products/strength/strong"><strong>Strong (8-12 mg)</strong></a> — Noticeable kick, popular with experienced users</li>
          <li><a href="/products/strength/extra-strong"><strong>Extra Strong (12-20 mg)</strong></a> — High intensity for heavy users</li>
          <li><a href="/products/strength/super-strong"><strong>Super Strong (20 mg+)</strong></a> — Maximum intensity from brands like Siberia and PABLO</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          If you are new to nicotine pouches, start with a light or normal strength and
          adjust upward as needed. It is much easier to move up in strength than to manage
          the discomfort of starting too high.
        </p>

        <h2>Popular Flavours</h2>
        <p>
          One of the biggest advantages of nicotine pouches over traditional tobacco products
          is the variety of flavours available:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><a href="/products/flavor/mint"><strong>Mint</strong></a> — The most popular flavour category by far, from peppermint to spearmint to icy menthol</li>
          <li><a href="/products/flavor/berry"><strong>Berry</strong></a> — Blueberry, strawberry, mixed berries, and wild forest blends</li>
          <li><a href="/products/flavor/citrus"><strong>Citrus</strong></a> — Orange, lemon, bergamot, and grapefruit</li>
          <li><a href="/products/flavor/coffee"><strong>Coffee</strong></a> — Espresso, mocha, and roasted bean flavours</li>
          <li><a href="/products/flavor/exotic"><strong>Exotic</strong></a> — Mango, passion fruit, watermelon, and other tropical flavours</li>
          <li><a href="/products/flavor/tobacco"><strong>Tobacco</strong></a> — Classic taste for those transitioning from traditional products</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to Use Nicotine Pouches</h2>
        <ol class="list-decimal pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Open the can</strong> and take one pouch</li>
          <li><strong>Place it</strong> between your upper lip and gum — either left or right side</li>
          <li><strong>Leave it in place</strong> for 20 to 40 minutes. You may feel a mild tingling — this is normal</li>
          <li><strong>Remove and dispose</strong> — most cans have a compartment in the lid for used pouches</li>
        </ol>
        <p>
          There is no need to chew, spit, or do anything else. The pouch works on its own.
          You can talk, drink water, and go about your day normally.
        </p>

        <h2>Who Uses Nicotine Pouches?</h2>
        <p>
          Nicotine pouches appeal to several groups:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Smokers looking to quit</strong> — Pouches provide nicotine without the harmful chemicals from combustion</li>
          <li><strong>Vapers seeking an alternative</strong> — No device, no charging, no liquid refills</li>
          <li><strong>Traditional snus users</strong> — Cleaner, no staining, wider flavour variety</li>
          <li><strong>Adults who want discretion</strong> — No smell, no visible use, usable anywhere</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Are Nicotine Pouches Legal in Europe?</h2>
        <p>
          Nicotine pouches are legal in most EU countries. Regulations vary by country — some
          markets classify them as consumer products, others as tobacco-related products with
          specific age and labelling requirements. In all cases, you must be at least 18 years
          old to purchase them.
        </p>

        <h2>Ready to Try?</h2>
        <p>
          With <a href="/nicotine-pouches">over 700 products from 91+ brands</a>, {tenant.name}
          has the largest selection of nicotine pouches in Europe. Not sure where to start?
          Take our <a href="/flavor-quiz">flavour quiz</a> for a personalised recommendation,
          or browse our <a href="/faq">FAQ</a> for more answers.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": title,
    "description": description,
    "datePublished": publishDate,
    "dateModified": publishDate,
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": tenant.name, "url": `https://${tenant.domain}` },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": tenant.name, "logo": { "@type": "ImageObject", "url": `https://${tenant.domain}/favicon.png` } },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": `https://${tenant.domain}/blog/what-are-nicotine-pouches` },
  })} />
</Shop>
